_source.body: New York Mayor Eric Adams gave a stern warning to Rep. Marjorie Taylor Greene to behave herself when she comes to the city. As Greene, to my knowledge, has never committed an act of violence, it seems to me that Adams should instead be addressing the thousands of violent criminals who plague his city every day. If he were as focused on all the murders, rapes, assaults, robberies, thefts, and vandalism as he is on a woman who has a big mouth, he might actually make his city safer.
